For how busy it gets, they do a great job of killing the line. The line is usually out the door during lunch rushes, but you honestly will wait no more than 10 minutes, which is great given how many people are in line. The food at this location is solid, and I cannot complain at all. Fries are salted pretty well, and the chicken sandwich is always hot and fresh since they are constantly making them to handle the lines.

They have great employees who take the orders quickly and get the food out quickly. It's a highly efficent cfa in terms of the time it takes for a customer to get in and the the time it takes for them to get their food. Over all of the times I've been here during a lunch rush, my order has never been wrong and the food was always to my cfa standards. The only thing they could improve on would be to maybe smile more and just bring that feeling of a family business to it. I understand it should be quick service, but it should also feel welcoming at all times to be considered a cfa.

Great place. When I arrived to Atlanta, this we my first stop for lunch. The fried chicken and bacon was amazing!! And the dressings! Oh my god. I have never been the kind of man that puts dressing on the food, but I tried every dressing and I was astonished! My favorite is the mustard bbq and the one with avocado. I defenitely recommend this place. Oh! And ask for a refill of you drink, because it's free!! I refill my lemonade and enjoyed in the hot summer day of Atlanta.
